14:47
Sharafat Karim
In reply to this message
This topic is made to share and showcase projects (academic/ non academic). Feel free to share anything, regardless of how little/ big it is.

Why sharing?

Coding can be challenging, but it can become a lot easier if you have the right strategies and tools. Maybe others can help you to figure out a different perspective or can collaborate with you to exceed the limits. Likewise, you can read others code and discuss to learn a different perspective of thinking.

Open source philosophy

Software is controlling everyones life, like not a lot other things. By having proprietary software standards (MS office, Windows, Google, WhatsApp, ...) These companies have more influence then our governments*. This is a situation everyone calls dramatically wrong, if they imaginate it actively, but we all are promoting this dystopia by using closed source software. A free and righteous world is not possible if there remains any proprietary standard. So it is our duty to use FLOSS.

With commercial software you are required to blindly trust the manufacturer. Trust that they will not abandon the software, exploit your data, store you data insecurely...etc..

Open source can be verified. Share the love of open source.

read more here (blogs),
- https://sharafat.pages.dev/software-telemetry-bangla/
- https://sharafat.pages.dev/git-intro/
- https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/introduction-to-open-source-and-its-benefits/

Sharing platforms?

Platforms with GIT/ SVN (version controlling ability) like GitHub, GitLab, BitBucket, docker/ podmain container is recommended. But replit or self hosting or perhaps directly sharing through zip is also welcomed. It's your choice! Doesn't really matter.

Physics students learn the speed of light, c, is the same for all inertial observers but no one has ever actually measured it in one direction. Thanks to Kiwico for sponsoring this video. For 50% off your first month of any crate, go to https://kiwico.com/veritasium50

from manim import *


class Fading(Scene):
    def construct(self):
        self.camera.background_color = WHITE
        text1 = Text("Ø¹ÙŠØ¯ Ù…Ø¨Ø§Ø±Ùƒ", color=BLACK, font="Arial_Rounded_MT_Bold_Bold")
        text2 = Text("Ğ˜Ğ´ ĞœÑƒĞ±Ğ°Ñ€Ğ°Ğº", color=BLACK, font = "sans-serif")
        text3 = Text("ã‚¨ã‚¤ãƒ‰ãƒ»ãƒ ãƒãƒ©ã‚¯", color=BLACK, font = "sans-serif")
        text4 = Text("BayramÄ±nÄ±z Kutlu Olsun", color=BLACK, font = "sans-serif")
        text5 = Text("à¤ˆà¤¦ à¤®à¥à¤¬à¤¾à¤°à¤•", color=BLACK, font = "sans-serif")
        text6 = Text("Bonne fÃªte de l'AÃ¯d", color=BLACK)
        text_final = Text("à¦ˆà¦¦ à¦®à§‹à¦¬à¦¾à¦°à¦•", color=BLACK)
        text_kazi = Text("#KaziRifatMorshed/CSEKU230220", color=BLACK)

        # tex_in = Tex("Fade", "In").scale(3)
        # tex_out = Tex("Fade", "Out").scale(3)
        self.play(FadeIn(text1, scale=2.5))
        self.wait(1)
        self.play(ReplacementTransform(text1, text2))
        self.wait(0.5)
        self.play(FadeOut(text2))
        self.play(FadeIn(text3, scale=0.5))
        self.wait(1)
        self.play(ReplacementTransform(text3, text4))
        self.wait(0.5)
        self.play(FadeTransform(text4,text5))
        self.wait(1)
        self.play(ReplacementTransform(text5,text6))
        self.wait(1)
        self.play(FadeOut(text6))

        self.play(DrawBorderThenFill(text_final, scale=2.66, stroke_color=BLACK))
        self.wait(0.5)
        self.play(ReplacementTransform(text_final, text_kazi))
        self.wait(1)

Recursion 
#include <stdio.h>
#define V 4
#define INF 99999

void printSolution(int dist[][V]);
void floydWarshall(int dist[][V])
{
    int i, j, k;

    for (k = 0; k < V; k++) {
        for (i = 0; i < V; i++) {
            for (j = 0; j < V; j++) {
                if (dist[i][k] + dist[k][j] < dist[i][j])
                    dist[i][j] = dist[i][k] + dist[k][j];
            }
        }
    }
    printSolution(dist);
}

void printSolution(int dist[][V])
{
    printf(
        "The following matrix shows the shortest distances"
        " between every pair of vertices \n");
    for (int i = 0; i < V; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < V; j++) {
            if (dist[i][j] == INF)
                printf("%7s", "INF");
            else
                printf("%7d", dist[i][j]);
        }
        printf("\n");
    }
}

int main()
{
    int graph[V][V] = { { 0, 5, INF, 10 },
                        { INF, 0, 3, INF },
                        { INF, INF, 0, 1 },
                        { INF, INF, INF, 0 } };
    floydWarshall(graph);
    return 0;
}

Cosmic Flare
To calculate the total assets, we need to add up all the asset transactions:

1. Common stock for cash: $10,000
2. Equipment purchased on account: $3,000
3. Legal services provided for cash: $1,500
4. Services provided to a client on account: $2,000

Total Assets:
$10,000 (common stock) + $3,000 (equipment) + $1,500 (cash from legal services) + $2,000 (accounts receivable from services provided) = $16,500

Therefore, the total assets amount to $16,500.
